- [ ] 4 Diced Chicken Thighs 
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Cornflour 
- [ ] 1 Tsp Rice Vinegar 
- [ ] 1 Tsp Soy Sauce 
- [ ] ¼ Tsp Chinese Five Spice
- [ ] ½ A Diced Red Pepper
- [ ] ½ A Diced Green Pepper
- [ ] 1 Onion
- [ ] 2 Crushed Garlic Cloves 
- [ ] 3 Tbsp Soy Sauce 
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Tomato Purée 
- [ ] 2 Tbsp Honey 
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Water
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Sesame Oil 

1. Add Chicken, Cornflour And a teaspoon of Soy Sauce to a bowl and mix together thoroughly, add to the air fryer for about 15 minutes.

2. Add the rest of the Soy Sauce, Water, Honey, Chilli Flakes, Tomato Purée, Garlic and Sesame Oil to a bowl and mix then set aside.

3. Then fry off your vegetables, add the sauce to the pan and then add in the cooked chicken and stir until the chicken is properly coated.
